<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-20T19:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-20T19:30:00-05:00" n="282" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.01/63: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-20T21:00:00-03:30">July 20, 1937—9
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>26. Department’s 15, July 19, 7 p.m.<note n="23" xml:id="d282fn23">See
                                footnote 14, <ref target="#pg_261">p. 261</ref>.</note> Reed<note n="24" xml:id="d282fn24">Leslie E. Reed, First Secretary of
                                Legation.</note> saw Foreign Minister who stated that he is not
                            aware of the receipt by his Legation at La Paz of officer referred to,
                            that as to recognition of new Government he instructed Uruguayan
                            Legation to associate itself with other powers signatory to Chaco
                            agreements and that he has no information <pb facs="0279" n="269" xml:id="pg_269"/> regarding stability, composition, authority or
                            popular support of the new Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>